# Copy to .env.lambda and fill in for your own Lambda Cloud account.
#
# Used by `./push.sh --mode lambda` (and any modulator's modulate_lambda.sh).
# Lambda Cloud has no projects/zones/IAM — just an API key + SSH key + a
# preference for which GPU type to launch.

# Generate at https://cloud.lambdalabs.com/api-keys (one-time, ~1 min)
LAMBDA_API_KEY=secret_api_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Name of the SSH key registered in Lambda Cloud (dashboard → SSH Keys).
# This is the *name* in Lambda's UI, not a path. The matching .pem lives at
# LAMBDA_SSH_KEY_PATH below.
LAMBDA_SSH_KEY_NAME=my_lambda_key

# Local path to the matching .pem private key. The launcher uses this for
# SCP/SSH into the provisioned instance. chmod 400 it; *.pem is gitignored.
LAMBDA_SSH_KEY_PATH=~/.ssh/my_lambda_key.pem

# ── GPU selection ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Two separate fallback lists — modulation and runtime have different
# optimal GPUs, so they don't share. The launcher tries each in order
# until one has capacity in any region.

# Modulation (./push.sh --lambda): A100-first.
# Training the ECM benefits from a real GPU; A100 is the cheapest tier
# with enough throughput. A10 is included as a final fallback if A100
# capacity is exhausted. Override to H100 for fastest training, e.g.:
#   LAMBDA_INSTANCE_TYPES=gpu_2x_h100_sxm5,gpu_1x_h100_sxm5,gpu_1x_a100
LAMBDA_INSTANCE_TYPES=gpu_1x_a100,gpu_1x_a100_sxm4,gpu_1x_a10

# Runtime (./run.sh --lambda): A10-first, H100s as last-resort fallback.
# Qwen-0.8B inference fits easily on an A10 (24 GB VRAM) and an A10
# costs ~$0.75/hr vs ~$1.99/hr for an A100 SXM4 — meaningful since
# runtime VMs are persistent. The launcher tries each type in order
# until one has capacity, so cheap-first ordering keeps the typical
# bill low while H100s prevent a hard fail when A10/A100 are exhausted.
LAMBDA_RUNTIME_INSTANCE_TYPES=gpu_1x_a10,gpu_1x_a100,gpu_1x_a100_sxm4,gpu_1x_h100_pcie,gpu_1x_h100_sxm5,gpu_2x_h100_sxm5

# Optional: API base override (uncomment for a non-public Lambda endpoint).
# LAMBDA_API_BASE=https://cloud.lambdalabs.com/api/v1
